Today's adventures with Enterprise Miner have, I think, finally pushed me over the tipping point with my Mac after several rounds of virtual machine issues. Anyone have a Windows computer they'd recommend?  I'm preferably looking for something lightweight (in pounds not power!)
<@U1KT2JJE8>: I was talking to Brandon yesterday about future computer investment and he had some really great advice based on just about any personal preferences!
<@U1KT2JJE8> I have a Dell Latitude E7470 and I like it a lot. It's pretty lightweight at 3.1 lbs
I have a Dell XPS 15 -- I've seen a couple of people with the lighter version (XPS 13). I love mine, and those with the 13-inch model seem to like theirs too!
I love my XPS 13
I have an HP Spectre that I think is pretty light and I love it.
I'm with <@U1L7E8GSU>.  Love my Spectre.
Ditto <@U1KRNHQA1> and my xps13.

<@U1KT2JJE8>  my priorities might be different than yours (I value cost efficiency and high performance over physical weight) but I'm very satisfied with my XPS 15.   What is "light weight" to you?   Due to Moore's law, you may find that if you're replacing an older laptop you can actually get something pretty powerful while still getting something lighter than you're used to.
<@U1KT2JJE8>  my 15 inch lenovo yoga is super light and was cheap for having a solid state drive and intel i7
